Credit Rating
resource.description: This table shows the percentage of the City of Santa Monica's outstanding debt receiving the highest possible rating from at least one rating agency.  Outstanding debt includes General Obligation (GO) bonds, lease revenue bonds, and revenue bonds.  Different debt types have different rating scales.  Santa Monica aims to have all outstanding debt of any type receive the highest possible rating every year.

resource.description: Carbon emissions are generated from the use of fossil fuels, primarily coal, natural gas, gasoline and diesel. Fossil fuels consumed at the community level as well as the City operations level are tracked and converted into carbon dioxide equivalents (metric tons or MTCO2e). The City develops plans, policies and programs to help reduce the carbon footprint of the community and its operations.
